values:
Well we won the battle its a nice feeling but is by no means a success I mean we won a battle of the bands in Salt Lake City against some punk bands and one other truelly genuine musical act.  But it was a good time.  We had a lot of friends there but I missed missy so bad! I wanted her there big time and she couldn't be it sucked but the gig was a blast! the crowd was into it and we grooved hard.  We had a ton of support from all our friends including my live journal buddy jesse
by the way if you read her post our website is www.theshadesofgray.com with a a not an e but its all good. Anyways will be writing soon I imagine who the hell am I talking too?

well jesse didn't think the shirt thing was so funny.

She is such an incredible writer I hear music as soon as I read her words thats really cool.

And in response the only tricks I am gonna pull tomarrow is that we are going to groove that place hard and I mean hard!

I was talking to jesse and I thought she didnt' have a shirt on
that was funny.

um she spilled beer on her once at the gallivan center and I we might have a show there next week....i hope she dosn't do it again.....

do you ever think that when we are driving we just are spinning the earth under our tires and we are just staying still?
